narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Knowledge: not much. Skills: Casey ran a little professional development workshop, and also explored some of the philosophical underpinnings of science. This was extremely interesting and Insights: I became better acquainted with the research program of each professor and gained a better understanding of how they may be an intellectual resource during my degree.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: direct contact with professors that may otherwise be difficult to reach. There aren't that many social events where we get to talk to professors specifically about their own research.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Some points of possible improvement were already articulated during the end of year meeting. I personally would prefer a little more structure - perhaps a mini lecture given by each professor on specific papers or discovery that they think were foundational to the ecological or evolutionary research of today.
